The paper deals with the computational complexity of Boolean functions, specifically those with low sensitivity. This topic falls under the area of computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses algorithms for computing these functions, which falls under the area of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also uses information theory (cs.IT) to establish a noise-stability guarantee for these functions. Finally, the paper discusses the structure of these functions, which could potentially involve computational geometry (cs.CG).
